Mix together the cream cheese, ricotta cheese, Splenda, vanilla extract and cinnamon. This can be done by hand, processor or mixer. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for a couple of hours or a day or two in advanced. When ready to serve. Rinse the berries with cold water and place in a bowl. Sprinkle 1 Tbsp of Splenda over the berries and lightly toss. Then remove the ricotta mixture from the refrigerator. Stir well. Loosely spoon the mixture into 4 wine glasses. Add the berries to the top and serve.